---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import DocsSidebar from "../../components/DocsSidebar.astro";
---
<Layout title="Quickstart · flipagent docs">
	<div class="cmw cmw-bordered">
		<div class="docs-shell">
			<DocsSidebar />
			<article class="docs-content">
				<h1>Quickstart</h1>
				<p class="lead">Five minutes from zero to your first deal scan.</p>

				<h2>1. Get an API key</h2>
				<p>
					<a href="/signup/">Sign up</a>. The free tier is 100 calls a month, no card required. Your dashboard issues a key in one click; copy it from the modal (it's only shown once).
				</p>
				<p>
					Self-hosting? Run the API in your own infrastructure and your dashboard will be at <code>your-host/dashboard/</code> instead. See <a href="/docs/self-host/">self-host</a>.
				</p>

				<h2>2a. From Claude Desktop (MCP)</h2>
				<p>Drop the snippet into <code>~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code> and restart Claude:</p>
				<div class="code">
					<div class="code-head"><div class="dot-row"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div><span>claude_desktop_config.json</span></div>
<pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "flipagent": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "flipagent-mcp"],
      "env": { "FLIPAGENT_API_KEY": "fa_free_xxx" }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>
				</div>
				<p>The same config works in Cursor (<code>.cursor/mcp.json</code>), Cline, Continue.dev, Zed, and Windsurf.</p>

				<h2>2b. From any HTTP client</h2>
				<div class="code">
					<div class="code-head"><div class="dot-row"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div><span>shell</span></div>
<pre><code>{`curl "https://api.flipagent.dev/v1/listings/search?q=canon%2050mm&limit=10" \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer fa_free_xxx"`}</code></pre>
				</div>

				<h2>2c. From Node / TypeScript</h2>
				<p><code>@flipagent/sdk</code> is a typed thin client. One namespace per resource, all under <code>/v1/*</code>:</p>
				<div class="code">
					<div class="code-head"><div class="dot-row"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div><span>node</span></div>
<pre><code>{`import { createFlipagentClient } from "@flipagent/sdk";

const client = createFlipagentClient({ apiKey: "fa_free_xxx" });

const results = await client.listings.search({ q: "canon 50mm", limit: 10 });
console.log(results.itemSummaries?.length, "active listings");`}</code></pre>
				</div>

				<h2>3. Score the deals</h2>
				<p>Server-side scoring runs on the API, so the math is identical regardless of language. Pass active listings and (optionally) sold comps; get back a ranked list:</p>
				<div class="code">
					<div class="code-head"><div class="dot-row"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div><span>node</span></div>
<pre><code>{`// Pull sold comps for the same keyword
const sold = await client.sold.search({ q: "canon 50mm", limit: 50 });

// Rank deals across the active search using the sold comps
const { deals } = await client.discover.deals({
  results,
  opts: { comps: sold.itemSummaries, minNetCents: 2000 },
});

for (const d of deals) {
  if (d.verdict.rating === "buy") console.log(d);
}

// Or evaluate a single listing
const verdict = await client.evaluate.listing({
  item: results.itemSummaries[0],
  opts: { comps: sold.itemSummaries },
});`}</code></pre>
				</div>

				<h2>Next</h2>
				<ul>
					<li><a href="/docs/api/">Full API reference</a>: every endpoint, every field.</li>
					<li><a href="/docs/mcp/">MCP server</a>: agent tools for Claude, Cursor, Cline.</li>
					<li><a href="/pricing/">Pricing</a>: when free runs out.</li>
				</ul>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
